name: n,n-dimethyldodecylamine oxide

Taking these considerations into account and comparing to similar compounds, the estimated increase due to the quaternary amine oxide group is approximately +40 degrees Celsius, while the N,N-dimethyl groups contribute an additional +10 degrees Celsius combined.
